    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Serenoa repens are multifaceted, with its anti-inflammatory effects attributed to the presence of saponins and flavonoids, which can help reduce swelling and pain in the prostate gland. The anti-androgenic properties of this plant make it useful in treating benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH), a condition where the prostate gland enlarges, compressing the urethra and interfering with urination, by inhibiting the conversion of testosterone to dihydrotestosterone (DHT). Additionally, Serenoa repens exhibits antioxidant properties, scavenging free radicals and protecting cells from oxidative damage, which can contribute to its therapeutic effects in treating various conditions. The antimicrobial properties of this plant make it useful in preventing infections and promoting wound healing, while its antiproliferative effects inhibit the growth of cancer cells, making it a potential agent in cancer treatment. The bioactive compounds responsible for these properties include flavonoids, saponins, and volatile oils, among others.",
