    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Serenoa repens are serenoa capsules which contain dried and powdered berries or leaves, serenoa tincture made by steeping dried berries or leaves in a solvent like ethanol, serenoa tea prepared by steeping dried berries or leaves in hot water, saw palmetto oil extracted from the fruit of Serenoa repens using a solvent or mechanical press, and serenoa oil obtained through cold-pressing of the fruit. These preparations are used to support prostate health due to the presence of phytosterols and fatty acids in Serenoa repens that may inhibit the conversion of testosterone to dihydrotestosterone. Serenoa repens may also have antioxidant properties that could protect against oxidative stress. The effectiveness of these preparations in reducing symptoms of benign prostatic hyperplasia has been supported by some clinical studies, although more research is needed to confirm these findings. The recommended dosage and preparation method may vary depending on the specific product and individual needs.",
